so found in France (mainly Lorraine and Alsace).","Danish: occupational name for a baker, from <i>bechere</i> ‘baker’.","Jewish (Ashkenazic): occupational name for a baker, from German <i>Bäcker</i> (compare 1 and   Backer  ) or Yiddish <i>beker</i> ‘baker’."],"variants":[{"name":"Backer","meanings":["German (<b>Bäcker</b>): variant of   Becker  . Compare   Baecker  .","Dutch: variant of   Bakker  . Compare   De Backer  .","Danish: probably of German origin (see 1 above)."]},{"name":"Beckers","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Ewald, Gerda, Hans, Klaus, Kurt, Wendelin, Wilhelmina.  French Jacques, Thierry.","Dutch, Flemish, and German: variant of   Becker   + the genitive case <i>-s</i>."]},{"name":"Baecker","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Siegfried, Bodo, Gerhardt, Heinz, Horst, Kurt, Waltraud.","German (mainly <b>Bäcker</b>): variant of   Becker  . Compare   Backer  ."]},{"name":"Beck","meanings":["English: topographic name for someone who lived beside a stream, from northern Middle English <i>bekke</i> ‘stream’ (Old Norse <i>bekkr</i>).","English (of Norman origin): habitational name from any of various places in northern France named Bec, for example Bec Hellouin in Eure, named with Old Norman French <i>bec</i> ‘stream’, from the same Old Norse root as in 1 above.","English: from the Middle English personal name <i>Becke</i> (Old English <i>Becca</i> or <i>Beocca</i>), of uncertain origin."]},{"name":"Beckerle","meanings":["South German: diminutive of   Becker  ."]},{"name":"De Beck","meanings":["Flemish: short form of <b>De Becker</b>, see   Becker  , or a variant of   Beckman  ."]},{"name":"Beckermann","meanings":["German: variant of   Becker   ‘baker’, formed with Middle High German <i>man</i> ‘man’."]}]},{"name":"Matthias","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament Greek form of the Hebrew name <i>Mattathia</i> (  see  Matthew  ), or rather of an Aramaic derivative. The Latin form of the name is <i>Matthaeus</i>. In English the form <i>Matthias</i> is used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament to distinguish the disciple who was chosen after the treachery of Judas to make up the twelve (Acts 1:23–26) from the evangelist <i>Matthew</i>. However, this distinction is not observed in other languages, where <i>Matthias</i> (or a version of it) is often a learned doublet existing alongside a vernacular derivative."],"variants":[{"name":"Mathias","meanings":["and Norwegian: learned doublet of   Mads ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Matthias Becker was born on 29 July 1603, in Hausen, Stuttgart, Württemberg, Germany, his father, Baltas Beckers, was 32 and his mother, Anna Maulick, was 25. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He was buried in Hausen, Stuttgart, Württemberg, Germany."},"et":{"29 July 1603–13 Aug 1603":"29. juuli 1603–13. august 1603","1603–1603":"1603–1603","1604–Male":"1604–Surnud","1645–Male":"1645–Surnud","1647–Female":"1647–Surnud","1572–Male":"1572–Surnud","1578–Female":"1578–Surnud","1645":"1645","1578":"1578","29 July 1603":"29. juuli 1603","1597":"1597","29 Jul 1603":"29. juuli 1603","1572":"1572","13 Aug 1603":"13. august 1603","1604":"1604","1647":"1647","1603":"1603","Hausen, Stuttgart, Württemberg, Deutschland":"Hausen, Stuttgart, Württemberg, Saksamaa","Hausen an der Zaber, Brackenheim, Württemberg, Deutschland":"Hausen an der Zaber, Kreis Brackenheim, Württemberg, Saksamaa","Hausen /Zaber (OA. Brackenheim), Württemberg, Germany":"Hausen, Stuttgart, Württemberg, Saksamaa"},"fi":{"29 July 1603–13 Aug 1603":"29. heinäkuuta 1603–13. elokuuta 1603","1603–1603":"1603–1603","1604–Male":"1604–Kuollut","1645–Male":"1645–Kuollut","1647–Female":"1647–Kuollut","1572–Male":"1572–Kuollut","1578–Female":"1578–Kuollut","1645":"1645","1578":"1578","29 July 1603":"29. heinäkuuta 1603","1597":"1597","29 Jul 1603":"29. heinäkuuta 1603","1572":"1572","13 Aug 1603":"13. elokuuta 1603","1